<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-87-1166 </DOCNO><TEXT>This report describes the activities of a program to increase energy efficiencyand promote conservation in the Canadian electrical/electronics industry.The companies participating in this program manufacture a variety ofproducts used in repoduction, transmission and generation of electricityand related electronic systems and components. Since 1975, energy efficiencyin this sector has improved 38%. Methods for achieving such efficiencyrange from simple housekeeping measures to energy management programswhich emphasize improved processes. 1 fig., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>